1
00:00:33,880 --> 00:00:34,640
MANTI

2
00:01:02,320 --> 00:01:05,200
Hi!

3
00:01:21,960 --> 00:01:23,039
How many doors did you add

4
00:01:23,039 --> 00:01:23,960
Two doors.

5
00:01:24,120 --> 00:01:25,400
It's all ruined on Friday night.

6
00:01:25,400 --> 00:01:26,720
Just be content.

7
00:01:26,720 --> 00:01:28,200
I don't know if I can finish my homework

8
00:01:28,200 --> 00:01:29,440
I don't know if I can finish my homework

9
00:01:30,760 --> 00:01:31,600
Ms. Song

10
00:01:31,760 --> 00:01:33,759
Everyone has to go home after school

11
00:01:34,080 --> 00:01:35,240
What about the chorus?

12
00:01:36,440 --> 00:01:38,840
How about I borrow two classes for my self-study class?

13
00:01:40,680 --> 00:01:42,360
When are you going to do your homework?

14
00:01:46,360 --> 00:01:48,320
Take out your textbook if you arrive.

15
00:01:48,640 --> 00:01:49,560
Ready for the morning reading.

16
00:01:58,240 --> 00:02:00,960
Gather the earth, the bell rings. The family of the Tripod.

17
00:02:08,720 --> 00:02:10,759
The earth is filled with spirits, the bell is ringing and the family is eating.

18
00:02:10,840 --> 00:02:12,400
This text is about...

19
00:02:20,920 --> 00:02:22,040
Sorry, everyone.

20
00:02:22,400 --> 00:02:23,720
This phone call may be important.

21
00:02:23,720 --> 00:02:24,760
Hold on.

22
00:02:32,520 --> 00:02:33,000
Hello.

23
00:02:34,440 --> 00:02:35,240
Song Chen.

24
00:02:35,920 --> 00:02:37,079
Your grandpa fell down.

25
00:02:39,920 --> 00:02:40,920
What?

26
00:02:41,880 --> 00:02:43,000
Grandpa fell down.

27
00:02:43,280 --> 00:02:44,680
He's still in a coma.

28
00:02:45,760 --> 00:02:47,160
He's not in a good condition.

29
00:02:47,840 --> 00:02:50,200
Prepare yourself.

30
00:02:50,920 --> 00:02:52,200
and come back.

31
00:03:44,920 --> 00:03:45,640
Let's go.

32
00:03:48,520 --> 00:03:49,520
We'll go back with you.

33
00:03:51,160 --> 00:03:52,800
There's a train at 1 p.m.

34
00:03:53,079 --> 00:03:54,360
It's not too late to hurry.

35
00:04:02,400 --> 00:04:02,960
But...

36
00:04:02,960 --> 00:04:04,800
I’ve asked Captain Guo for you.

37
00:04:04,800 --> 00:04:06,640
He said we'll talk about the application when he comes back.

38
00:04:06,640 --> 00:04:07,320
You go first.

39
00:04:07,960 --> 00:04:09,960
I'll keep an eye on Class 1 for you.

40
00:04:19,839 --> 00:04:21,839
Send them the review materials

41
00:04:22,640 --> 00:04:23,760
to them.

42
00:04:24,360 --> 00:04:24,880
Okay.

43
00:05:01,720 --> 00:05:02,360
Hello?

44
00:05:20,640 --> 00:05:21,600
Grandpa is awake.

45
00:05:22,960 --> 00:05:23,760
He's awake.

46
00:05:24,160 --> 00:05:25,360
That means he's fine.

47
00:05:26,160 --> 00:05:27,760
He just talked to me.

48
00:05:28,560 --> 00:05:29,600
That's good.

49
00:05:30,120 --> 00:05:31,440
You scared me.

50
00:05:31,560 --> 00:05:33,280
I didn't dare to talk.

51
00:05:34,200 --> 00:05:35,520
Is that the tea house by the road?

52
00:05:38,960 --> 00:05:40,680
That's a mahjong parlor.

53
00:05:40,680 --> 00:05:42,240
My grandma used to go there often.

54
00:05:42,440 --> 00:05:43,480
Should I...

55
00:05:43,880 --> 00:05:45,400
You came all the way here

56
00:05:45,400 --> 00:05:47,440
to play mahjong with people over 70.

57
00:05:47,640 --> 00:05:48,560
Are you serious?

58
00:05:49,440 --> 00:05:50,840
I don't want to be bored.

59
00:05:50,840 --> 00:05:51,960
Grandpa is awake too.

60
00:05:51,960 --> 00:05:53,040
We came to this big village

61
00:05:53,040 --> 00:05:54,680
we can't help out with the work.

62
00:05:56,760 --> 00:05:57,840
Are we almost there?

63
00:06:14,160 --> 00:06:14,760
Chen.

64
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:16,280
Many people came back from your home.

65
00:06:16,760 --> 00:06:17,600
That's a lot.

66
00:06:17,600 --> 00:06:19,360
Didn't 200 people get up during Chinese New Year?

67
00:06:19,600 --> 00:06:20,560
200 people?

68
00:06:21,280 --> 00:06:23,120
You know Chaoshan family gathering.

69
00:06:23,240 --> 00:06:25,040
Our generation is not popular anymore.

70
00:06:25,480 --> 00:06:27,160
Can your grandpa recognize so many people?

71
00:06:27,480 --> 00:06:28,360
No.

72
00:06:28,520 --> 00:06:29,880
So it's all in number

73
00:06:30,120 --> 00:06:31,160
From my dad and brother.

74
00:06:31,160 --> 00:06:32,680
He is 101. My dad is 601.

75
00:06:32,680 --> 00:06:33,880
I'm Room 605.

76
00:06:45,560 --> 00:06:46,360
Chen.

77
00:06:47,040 --> 00:06:47,960
This is Chen.

78
00:06:48,360 --> 00:06:49,880
Gosh, you've grown so tall.

79
00:06:49,880 --> 00:06:51,360
I haven't seen you for years.

80
00:06:51,440 --> 00:06:52,240
Aunt.

81
00:06:52,600 --> 00:06:53,480
Where are your grandparents?

82
00:06:53,600 --> 00:06:54,840
They are on their way back.

83
00:06:54,840 --> 00:06:55,920
Your grandpa just left the hospital.

84
00:06:56,440 --> 00:06:58,000
He's fine.

85
00:06:58,600 --> 00:07:00,600
Look, we're talking. We're here.

86
00:07:09,840 --> 00:07:10,600
Grandpa, Grandma.

87
00:07:10,600 --> 00:07:11,400
Chen is back.

88
00:07:11,400 --> 00:07:12,080
Slow down.

89
00:07:13,480 --> 00:07:15,760
How is grandpa? Where did you fall?

90
00:07:15,760 --> 00:07:18,400
I'm fine. I just broke my leg.

91
00:07:19,280 --> 00:07:21,520
I'm old and useless.

92
00:07:21,520 --> 00:07:23,240
Don't you need another check-up at the hospital?

93
00:07:23,240 --> 00:07:24,320
I think so too.

94
00:07:24,400 --> 00:07:25,920
Grandpa heard you're back.

95
00:07:25,920 --> 00:07:27,160
He insists on going home.

96
00:07:27,200 --> 00:07:30,160
Let grandma see if you've lost weight again.

97
00:07:30,920 --> 00:07:32,480
I'm not thin, Grandma. I've gained weight.

98
00:07:32,520 --> 00:07:33,840
It's good to be fat.

99
00:07:33,960 --> 00:07:35,520
I'll be relieved if I gain weight.

100
00:07:36,560 --> 00:07:38,320
You even got a helper.

101
00:07:39,080 --> 00:07:40,120
Grandpa, be careful.

102
00:07:40,120 --> 00:07:41,400
What help?

103
00:07:41,400 --> 00:07:42,640
Don't you recognize them?

104
00:07:46,080 --> 00:07:47,360
Miaomiao.

105
00:07:48,520 --> 00:07:49,600
You're a grown girl.

106
00:07:49,920 --> 00:07:52,120
You're really different when you work.

107
00:07:52,480 --> 00:07:54,800
Grandma almost didn't recognize you.

108
00:07:54,800 --> 00:07:55,800
Hello, Grandma.

109
00:07:55,800 --> 00:07:56,360
Okay.

110
00:07:58,920 --> 00:08:01,320
This long hair is called

111
00:08:01,840 --> 00:08:02,840
What Wei?

112
00:08:03,880 --> 00:08:04,680
Wei.

113
00:08:05,000 --> 00:08:06,160
Don't remind me.

114
00:08:06,160 --> 00:08:08,440
I can remember his name.

115
00:08:08,440 --> 00:08:10,280
Lin Jiawei, right?

116
00:08:11,720 --> 00:08:12,920
I've combined you two.

117
00:08:13,640 --> 00:08:14,880
My name is Chen Jiawei.

118
00:08:14,880 --> 00:08:15,760
His name is Lin Gou.

119
00:08:17,080 --> 00:08:18,560
Hello, Grandma. I'm Lin Haoran.

120
00:08:18,920 --> 00:08:21,240
Lin Jiaran.

121
00:08:21,280 --> 00:08:23,560
I remember.

122
00:08:25,840 --> 00:08:27,120
This one at the back.

123
00:08:27,520 --> 00:08:28,480
Grandma, stop acting.

124
00:08:28,480 --> 00:08:29,720
You must remember him.

125
00:08:29,840 --> 00:08:30,720
That's right.

126
00:08:31,440 --> 00:08:33,080
Isn't this Jing Xuan?

127
00:08:33,640 --> 00:08:35,320
The one who went to study in America.

128
00:08:36,440 --> 00:08:38,080
Li Xuan.

129
00:08:38,440 --> 00:08:39,600
You've changed a lot.

130
00:08:39,840 --> 00:08:41,120
He looks handsome again.

131
00:08:42,440 --> 00:08:44,000
Can anyone give me the travel fee?

132
00:08:44,320 --> 00:08:45,640
And this wheelchair rental fee.

133
00:08:45,640 --> 00:08:46,520
It's 200 won.

134
00:08:47,640 --> 00:08:49,880
It's 200 won. Are you robbing me?

135
00:08:50,240 --> 00:08:51,760
It's the same price.

136
00:08:52,040 --> 00:08:52,600
This is an ambulance, not a taxi.

137
00:08:52,680 --> 00:08:53,000
This is an ambulance, not a taxi.

138
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:54,080
This is an ambulance, not a taxi.

139
00:08:54,520 --> 00:08:56,040
It can't be so expensive. Don't order too much.

140
00:08:56,280 --> 00:08:57,040
Make it cheaper.

141
00:08:57,080 --> 00:08:57,760
It'll be fine.

142
00:08:57,920 --> 00:09:00,080
They can't get a taxi in front of the hospital.

143
00:09:00,240 --> 00:09:01,800
We agreed on the price.

144
00:09:02,040 --> 00:09:02,920
Mom,

145
00:09:04,800 --> 00:09:06,520
This old man is a fool.

146
00:09:06,640 --> 00:09:07,840
How can it count?

147
00:09:07,840 --> 00:09:09,160
Lower

148
00:09:10,000 --> 00:09:11,600
No, I'll pay.

149
00:09:13,440 --> 00:09:15,840
Chen made a lot of money in Shenzhen.

150
00:09:16,480 --> 00:09:17,720
So generous.

151
00:09:18,520 --> 00:09:20,040
You drove so many cars back.

152
00:09:20,320 --> 00:09:21,800
Didn't anyone pick up your grandparents?

153
00:09:21,800 --> 00:09:23,320
We need to cook.

154
00:09:23,520 --> 00:09:24,760
So many people are here.

155
00:09:25,040 --> 00:09:26,440
We have to entertain them.

156
00:09:26,560 --> 00:09:27,480
You must be hungry.

157
00:09:27,720 --> 00:09:29,280
Come with me.

158
00:09:29,280 --> 00:09:30,840
I'll get you some food.

159
00:09:44,280 --> 00:09:45,240
It's still the same.

160
00:09:45,480 --> 00:09:47,040
Braised fish is amazing.

161
00:09:47,680 --> 00:09:48,560
That's good.

162
00:09:48,840 --> 00:09:51,200
I'm happy as long as you enjoy the food.

163
00:09:52,120 --> 00:09:53,480
By the way, Chen,

164
00:09:54,400 --> 00:09:56,400
It's rare that we're all at home.

165
00:09:56,720 --> 00:10:00,720
I want to celebrate your grandpa's 80th birthday in advance.

166
00:10:00,960 --> 00:10:02,240
What do you think?

167
00:10:02,320 --> 00:10:04,920
Grandma, isn't grandpa 80 at the end of the year?

168
00:10:05,160 --> 00:10:06,600
It doesn't matter.

169
00:10:06,760 --> 00:10:08,480
Is your school in a hurry?

170
00:10:08,480 --> 00:10:09,800
If not,

171
00:10:09,800 --> 00:10:12,000
let's have dinner tomorrow night, okay?

172
00:10:13,240 --> 00:10:13,880
Okay.

173
00:10:14,560 --> 00:10:15,600
Since I'm back,

174
00:10:15,800 --> 00:10:17,200
I'll definitely be there for grandpa's birthday.

175
00:10:17,920 --> 00:10:19,040
That's great.

176
00:10:19,560 --> 00:10:22,400
I'll leave tomorrow's birthday banquet to you.

177
00:10:23,000 --> 00:10:24,960
What? Leave it to me.

178
00:10:25,200 --> 00:10:27,400
I want to eat a table of your cooking.

179
00:10:28,320 --> 00:10:30,160
Take it easy. Don't blow up the kitchen.

180
00:10:32,360 --> 00:10:34,160
Grandma, I can't cook at all.

181
00:10:34,400 --> 00:10:35,560
Can't I order takeout?

182
00:10:36,480 --> 00:10:38,920
There's no delivery in this small place.

183
00:10:40,720 --> 00:10:42,840
You order takeout every day in Shenzhen.

184
00:10:42,840 --> 00:10:44,200
That's what I'm worried about.

185
00:10:44,200 --> 00:10:45,080
No.

186
00:10:45,400 --> 00:10:46,880
Let's eat a big pot of rice.

187
00:10:47,000 --> 00:10:48,720
It's made by water. It smells good.

188
00:10:49,560 --> 00:10:51,440
But you can't always rely on others.

189
00:10:51,640 --> 00:10:52,960
Only when you learn it,

190
00:10:52,960 --> 00:10:54,040
That's the real skill.

191
00:10:54,400 --> 00:10:55,520
It's a deal.

192
00:10:55,720 --> 00:10:58,600
Cook a table for me and grandpa tomorrow night.

193
00:10:58,720 --> 00:10:59,960
There's no need to eat too much.

194
00:11:00,280 --> 00:11:03,640
Just learn what you like to eat.

195
00:11:04,680 --> 00:11:05,960
No, Grandma.

196
00:11:08,040 --> 00:11:09,520
It's my favorite

197
00:11:10,160 --> 00:11:11,320
Is it cold cumber

198
00:11:18,240 --> 00:11:19,240
One mackerel

199
00:11:19,480 --> 00:11:22,000
Three yellow chickens with enough horses.

200
00:11:22,960 --> 00:11:24,480
What do you mean by that?

201
00:11:24,520 --> 00:11:25,560
It's about me right now.

202
00:11:26,640 --> 00:11:28,480
But your grandma is quite thoughtful.

203
00:11:28,480 --> 00:11:30,240
She turned this party into a birthday party.

204
00:11:31,800 --> 00:11:32,840
Don't tell me...

205
00:11:33,800 --> 00:11:34,800
You think so too?

206
00:11:35,600 --> 00:11:36,760
It's not impossible.

207
00:11:37,400 --> 00:11:39,960
Didn't your dad say it was serious on the phone?

208
00:11:39,960 --> 00:11:42,040
But grandpa looked like he sprained his ankle.

209
00:11:45,120 --> 00:11:45,960
Speaking of which,

210
00:11:47,960 --> 00:11:49,320
I haven't seen your dad yet.

211
00:11:50,200 --> 00:11:51,080
Who knows?

212
00:11:51,520 --> 00:11:53,440
Maybe he went back

213
00:11:53,640 --> 00:11:54,720
he'll go back halfway.

214
00:11:59,680 --> 00:12:01,400
Boss, do you have any mackerel?

215
00:12:01,480 --> 00:12:03,240
Yes it's wild

216
00:12:04,440 --> 00:12:05,760
How big is that

217
00:12:06,080 --> 00:12:07,120
How about 3 kg?

218
00:12:09,560 --> 00:12:10,400
How big is 3 kg

219
00:12:10,800 --> 00:12:11,680
Three kilos is too big.

220
00:12:11,680 --> 00:12:13,000
The wild ones are not that big.

221
00:12:14,280 --> 00:12:15,200
Boss, do you think

222
00:12:15,200 --> 00:12:16,720
we are outsiders?

223
00:12:16,880 --> 00:12:18,120
Wildlife is not that big.

224
00:12:18,400 --> 00:12:20,400
Yes I just caught them this morning

225
00:12:20,640 --> 00:12:21,880
But there are small ones too

226
00:12:22,400 --> 00:12:23,160
More expensive

227
00:12:23,840 --> 00:12:25,120
Why is the small one more expensive

228
00:12:25,520 --> 00:12:26,880
It's hard to catch small ones.

229
00:12:27,320 --> 00:12:29,000
The small one should be wild. The small one.

230
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:30,840
We want the small one.

231
00:12:32,320 --> 00:12:33,480
The one that can swim.

232
00:12:33,880 --> 00:12:34,640
That one.

233
00:12:35,640 --> 00:12:37,400
Just ask your wife to buy it.

234
00:12:37,400 --> 00:12:38,200
She knows so much.

235
00:12:42,000 --> 00:12:42,720
This?

236
00:12:44,280 --> 00:12:44,880
How much is it?

237
00:12:45,480 --> 00:12:46,000
40 won.

238
00:12:47,320 --> 00:12:47,960
20 won.

239
00:12:48,080 --> 00:12:49,520
We don't bargain.

240
00:12:50,240 --> 00:12:51,400
But since you're so handsome,

241
00:12:51,520 --> 00:12:52,520
I'll give you five yuan at most.

242
00:12:52,520 --> 00:12:53,760
35 yuan, okay?

243
00:12:53,800 --> 00:12:55,200
I won't take it if it's over 25 won.

244
00:12:56,680 --> 00:12:57,720
Let's each give in.

245
00:12:58,760 --> 00:12:59,760
How about 30 yuan, beauty?

246
00:13:00,040 --> 00:13:01,480
It's open today. I'll give it to you.

247
00:13:01,480 --> 00:13:02,880
Let's go.

248
00:13:03,160 --> 00:13:04,480
25 dollars 25 yuan

249
00:13:06,520 --> 00:13:07,880
I can't do this business anymore.

250
00:13:09,760 --> 00:13:10,560
Not bad.

251
00:13:11,200 --> 00:13:12,840
You even pretended to leave.

252
00:13:13,680 --> 00:13:14,880
I was wondering

253
00:13:14,880 --> 00:13:16,160
in the same place as my grandma?

254
00:13:16,280 --> 00:13:17,880
The bargaining skills are so consistent.

255
00:13:18,000 --> 00:13:19,760
My wisdom of life

256
00:13:20,080 --> 00:13:22,080
Or the food you pay every day

257
00:13:22,080 --> 00:13:22,880
is not enough to fill your teeth.

258
00:13:23,760 --> 00:13:25,440
Okay, the experts have shown it.

259
00:13:25,440 --> 00:13:26,680
Do the next round by yourself.

260
00:13:27,520 --> 00:13:28,640
It seems so hard.

261
00:13:28,640 --> 00:13:29,360
It's spinning, boss.

262
00:13:29,360 --> 00:13:30,080
Okay.

263
00:13:30,080 --> 00:13:30,840
I'm leaving. Thank you.

264
00:13:30,840 --> 00:13:31,840
Come back when you're done.

265
00:13:34,160 --> 00:13:34,600
Boss

266
00:13:35,200 --> 00:13:36,000
Give me a scallion.

267
00:13:39,960 --> 00:13:41,120
Give me a scallion.

268
00:13:41,800 --> 00:13:43,320
I understand, handsome.

269
00:13:43,880 --> 00:13:46,040
This is not green onion but chives

270
00:13:50,080 --> 00:13:50,880
Isn't this green onion

271
00:13:51,280 --> 00:13:53,280
Don't you usually put scallion like this?

272
00:13:55,640 --> 00:13:56,960
Doesn't it look the same?

273
00:13:56,960 --> 00:13:58,040
It's normal to admit your mistake.

274
00:13:58,440 --> 00:13:59,240
Here you go.

275
00:13:59,680 --> 00:14:00,440
It does look similar.

276
00:14:00,440 --> 00:14:02,360
Because it's not green onion but garlic

277
00:14:03,720 --> 00:14:04,680
This is green onion.

278
00:14:06,080 --> 00:14:07,400
Do you think I've never been educated?

279
00:14:07,720 --> 00:14:09,360
The green onions and garlic are white.

280
00:14:09,360 --> 00:14:10,360
Can't I tell?

281
00:14:11,680 --> 00:14:12,480
How much is it, boss?

282
00:14:14,840 --> 00:14:16,880
Are you the grandson of the Song family?

283
00:14:18,360 --> 00:14:21,280
I think it's cheaper.

284
00:14:21,680 --> 00:14:23,920
If so, I'll give you the green onions.

285
00:14:24,120 --> 00:14:26,080
Your grandma often buys vegetables with me.

286
00:14:26,160 --> 00:14:27,280
Just a handful of green onions.

